By ABBAS BAMALLI KATSINA- Sen. Ahmed Kaita, has picked the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) ticket for Katsina North Senate seat at the National Assembly.Alhaji Aminu Bello, the Chairman, PDP Electoral Committee for Katsina State said this on Tuesday in Katsina at the end of the party primary election.He said that Kaita won the ticket unopposed as he was the only aspirant for the election.Speaking, Kaita expressed gratitude to God for helping him to secure the ticket as well as the delegates who found him worthy of the position.“Since I defected to the party, I have received tremendous support and hospitality from all and sundry,” he said.Kaita, who defected from the All Progressives Congress (APC) after winning on its platform, promised effective representation for the constituents if elected in 2023.“I am using this opportunity to call on aspirants who won and those who lost to remain united as members of one PDP family.“And they should also give all the needed support for the emergence of the party in 2023,’’ Kaita said.Alhaji Salisu Majigiri, the state PDP governorship aspirant, advised the electorate to vote for candidates based on merit and credibility in 2023.(NAN) Abuja - No fewer than 30 senators may not make it back to the parliament in 2023 when the 10th National Assembly would be inaugurated.  While some are pursuing other aspirations, paving the way for other aspirants to take over their seats in the Red Chamber, the re-election bids of… In "Top Stories" Abuja - The opposition Peoples Democratic Party on Wednesday extended the deadline for the submission of forms for a fourth time. However, impeccable sources in the PDP told The PUNCH that the party decided to extend the sale of forms in order to accommodate defectors from the All Progressives Congress… In "Top Stories" By OLAWALE JOKOTOYE   •Bukola Saraki Abeokuta- Former Senate President, Bukola Saraki, on Monday visited Ogun State to seek the support of delegates ahead of the May 28 Presidential primar